  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Tip: keep the <strong>goat's cheese</strong> in the refrigerator until step 5</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>pasta</strong> to a large pot with plenty of&nbsp;boiled water and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 8-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot with a splash of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic </strong></p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in&nbsp;300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span> boiled water with&nbsp;the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;oregano</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>- this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;the<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> to&nbsp;a&nbsp;dry, wide-based pan over a medium heat and cook&nbsp;for&nbsp;2-3 min or until toasted and lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Zest the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter!)</p>\r\n<p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut in half</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer&nbsp;the toasted <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> to a medium bowl</p>\r\n<p>Add the chopped <strong>parsley</strong>, <strong>lemon zest</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and&nbsp;1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>lemon juice</strong> to the bowl and mix well</p>\r\n<p>Cut the remaining<strong> lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/725.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crumble the <strong>goat's cheese</strong> into the bowl with the seasoned <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> and mix together</p>\r\n<p>You will have breadcrumbs left over, which you'll use at the end&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
